      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model and Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis power law are used. Literature support for SST at pump Reynolds numbers is available. However, the Giersiepen-Wurzinger law is known to overpredict NIH at high shear exposure times, and no DNS reference data at VAD shear regimes was used to validate model form. Achieved level 2 reflects limited model form justification at MRL 5 requirements."
